WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.125 --> 00:00:11.416
THIS FILM IS FICTION.

2
00:00:11.500 --> 00:00:12.791
ARE HAPPENING DO NOT DESCRIBE -

3
00:00:12.875 --> 00:00:13.833
REAL PLACES. REAL CHARACTERS.

4
00:00:13.916 --> 00:00:14.875
LANGUAGES. COSTUMES. ETC.

5
00:05:05.583 --> 00:05:06.583
Yes.

6
00:05:08.416 --> 00:05:09.666
- Great!
- Well done!

7
00:05:10.166 --> 00:05:11.333
Yes.

8
00:05:11.416 --> 00:05:12.458
Your turn.

9
00:05:13.833 --> 00:05:15.083
- About.
- Go ahead.

10
00:05:16.125 --> 00:05:17.000
Yes!

11
00:05:19.166 --> 00:05:20.041
Fola. leave it!

12
00:05:23.083 --> 00:05:24.125
Good!

13
00:05:30.958 --> 00:05:32.416
I told you!

14
00:05:32.500 --> 00:05:34.291
PLAYER 1: 15 3
PLAYER 2: 30 3

15
00:05:34.916 --> 00:05:37.666
A win for team two.

16
00:05:37.750 --> 00:05:39.250
Thank you.

17
00:05:39.333 --> 00:05:40.458
- We won!
- Don't worry.

18
00:05:40.541 --> 00:05:42.041
We will win next time.

19
00:05:42.125 --> 00:05:44.958
- Don't worry.
- Next time. then.

20
00:05:45.041 --> 00:05:47.958
- Tade. is that you?
- Next time. then.

21
00:05:49.250 --> 00:05:50.291
- Sweetheart.
- Hardly.

22
00:05:50.375 --> 00:05:52.416
- Really?
- We're going to win.

23
00:05:52.500 --> 00:05:53.375
Leave them alone.

24
00:06:06.958 --> 00:06:09.666
Keep up the good work! That's it!

25
00:06:09.750 --> 00:06:11.166
This is how the winners dance.

26
00:06:24.375 --> 00:06:25.791
The winners are here!

27
00:06:28.750 --> 00:06:30.000
I see.

28
00:06:31.208 --> 00:06:32.208
What is it now?

29
00:06:37.250 --> 00:06:40.291
Fola. why the long face?

30
00:06:40.375 --> 00:06:41.500
Why are you sulking?

31
00:06:42.250 --> 00:06:43.833
Is it because you lost?

32
00:06:45.583 --> 00:06:46.666
Listen.

33
00:06:47.958 --> 00:06:51.958
In life. sometimes you win and sometimes you lose.

34
00:06:52.791 --> 00:06:55.041
Today you lost. tomorrow you might win.

35
00:06:56.541 --> 00:07:01.541
The most important thing is that we win in love.

36
00:07:02.291 --> 00:07:03.125
Or what?

37
00:07:03.208 --> 00:07:04.208
Okay. Mom.

38
00:07:04.291 --> 00:07:05.291
Smile now.

39
00:07:06.291 --> 00:07:07.291
Is that all you can shed?

40
00:07:09.750 --> 00:07:11.500
- Thank you. darling.
- Thank you.

41
00:07:11.583 --> 00:07:12.875
You are love.

42
00:07:12.958 --> 00:07:14.250
Thank you.

43
00:07:14.333 --> 00:07:18.750
- God created us to love.
- True.

44
00:07:18.833 --> 00:07:20.541
You I will always call my love.

45
00:07:21.291 --> 00:07:22.541
for you are a gift from God.

46
00:07:22.625 --> 00:07:23.875
- Thank you.
- Thank you. dear.

47
00:07:25.125 --> 00:07:26.625
- Thank you very much.
- Thank you.

48
00:07:26.708 --> 00:07:28.333
- Yes.
- So.

49
00:07:28.875 --> 00:07:32.625
- Let's not worry about losing.
- Yes.

50
00:07:33.500 --> 00:07:35.541
We will soon know the winner.

51
00:07:35.625 --> 00:07:36.916
- Which one?
- Let's dance.

52
00:07:37.000 --> 00:07:38.375
Stop it already.

53
00:07:38.958 --> 00:07:40.625
- Stop.
- I'm teaching you...

54
00:07:40.708 --> 00:07:41.916
- to dance.
- You know.

55
00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:43.375
- that I can beat you.
- Let's see.

56
00:07:43.458 --> 00:07:45.708
- Come on. Fola.
- Let's see.

57
00:07:45.791 --> 00:07:47.708
Tade. this time.

58
00:07:49.625 --> 00:07:53.125
- Swing your hips.
- Okay.

59
00:07:55.583 --> 00:07:57.083
That's what I taught you.

60
00:07:58.125 --> 00:08:01.583
Let's dance.

61
00:08:08.333 --> 00:08:13.791
- You can't tear down my house!
- Look!

62
00:08:19.791 --> 00:08:21.250
Break it down!

63
00:08:27.833 --> 00:08:30.416
Break it all up! Scrap all that!

64
00:08:30.500 --> 00:08:32.166
Break it down!

65
00:08:32.250 --> 00:08:33.666
Scatter to the ground.

66
00:08:33.750 --> 00:08:35.583
And you will be destroyed with it.

67
00:08:35.666 --> 00:08:38.458
You can't tear down my house!

68
00:08:39.333 --> 00:08:40.916
Break it down!

69
00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:42.666
Don't tear down my house.

70
00:09:07.083 --> 00:09:08.916
Buy cheese!

71
00:09:09.416 --> 00:09:10.458
Come on out.

72
00:09:13.750 --> 00:09:17.125
You are confused. young man.

73
00:09:17.791 --> 00:09:21.166
A crowd that wants to party

74
00:09:25.208 --> 00:09:26.166
If we...

75
00:09:27.291 --> 00:09:29.750
Don't you know you're at Otunba's house?

76
00:09:31.791 --> 00:09:32.708
What's wrong with you?

77
00:09:34.583 --> 00:09:35.833
Here you come -

78
00:09:35.916 --> 00:09:37.791
and drive like a madman.

79
00:09:38.291 --> 00:09:39.583
He is mentally ill.

80
00:09:39.666 --> 00:09:40.916
- Chief?
- Yes?

81
00:09:41.000 --> 00:09:42.791
- I'm here to see you.
- What is it?

82
00:09:42.875 --> 00:09:44.250
I hear you're tearing down houses.

83
00:09:44.875 --> 00:09:47.375
Oh. you mean? That's what we do.

84
00:09:47.458 --> 00:09:49.041
He is confused.

85
00:09:49.125 --> 00:09:51.750
- He doesn't know how to express himself.
- And you enjoy it.

86
00:09:52.500 --> 00:09:54.583
When you sell these countries.

87
00:09:54.666 --> 00:09:56.291
would you sell land in heaven?

88
00:09:56.375 --> 00:09:58.416
- Your father.
- Did you destroy my father's house?

89
00:09:59.333 --> 00:10:02.041
The house I worked so hard to build?

90
00:10:02.125 --> 00:10:03.500
Are you now arguing.

91
00:10:03.583 --> 00:10:06.250
you don't know.
when I got the land and paid for it?

92
00:10:06.333 --> 00:10:07.333
We don't know.

93
00:10:07.416 --> 00:10:08.791
The authorities are intervening.

94
00:10:08.875 --> 00:10:10.375
You're not going to be OK.

95
00:10:10.458 --> 00:10:11.291
So be it.

96
00:10:11.375 --> 00:10:13.041
- So be it.
- It's not going to be okay.

97
00:10:13.125 --> 00:10:14.458
- So be it!
- For whom -

98
00:10:14.541 --> 00:10:16.375
- you talk like that?
- No problem.

99
00:10:16.458 --> 00:10:19.083
I ask. We are the chiefs of Ilara.

100
00:10:19.166 --> 00:10:21.375
- The chiefs of Ilaras are like kings.
- True.

101
00:10:21.458 --> 00:10:23.625
- Even higher-ranking ones!
- You. your parents.

102
00:10:23.708 --> 00:10:26.541
- and those countries. Who owns them?
- We do.

103
00:10:26.625 --> 00:10:28.000
You would be grateful.

104
00:10:28.083 --> 00:10:30.416
that you were not inside the house.
when it was demolished.

105
00:10:30.500 --> 00:10:31.416
Would you have done so?

106
00:10:31.500 --> 00:10:32.833
- Absolutely.
- You wouldn't dare.

107
00:10:32.916 --> 00:10:35.083
Let him act like he's bigger than you...

108
00:10:35.166 --> 00:10:39.208
than it is. Let me tell you.

109
00:10:39.291 --> 00:10:40.541
They want you to die.

110
00:10:40.625 --> 00:10:43.041
If you wish. you can
go to the police to complain.

111
00:10:43.125 --> 00:10:46.375
- You'll get out of breath.
- Yes.

112
00:10:46.458 --> 00:10:47.291
Can I get out of my life?

113
00:10:47.375 --> 00:10:48.916
- You will die.
- Yes.

114
00:10:49.000 --> 00:10:50.375
- Am I dead?
- You're going to die.

115
00:10:50.458 --> 00:10:52.166
You've been doing this long enough.

116
00:10:52.250 --> 00:10:53.125
That's enough.

117
00:10:53.208 --> 00:10:55.208
- You can't help it.
- Do you want to beat him?

118
00:10:55.291 --> 00:10:56.791
You've got away with it...

119
00:10:56.875 --> 00:10:57.791
long enough.

120
00:10:57.875 --> 00:10:58.750
Believe me when I say.

121
00:10:58.833 --> 00:10:59.708
You can't help it.

122
00:10:59.791 --> 00:11:00.791
We shall see!

123
00:11:00.875 --> 00:11:02.083
- We shall see!
- You can't!

124
00:11:02.166 --> 00:11:04.041
- We shall see!
- He's ruining the car.

125
00:11:04.125 --> 00:11:05.416
Do you want to?
-Check it out!

126
00:11:05.500 --> 00:11:06.458
This means war.

127
00:11:06.541 --> 00:11:08.041
Let me tell you...

128
00:11:37.708 --> 00:11:38.958
Thank you.

129
00:11:40.666 --> 00:11:42.500
- I am grateful.
- Good luck.

130
00:11:42.583 --> 00:11:43.458
Thank you.

131
00:11:43.541 --> 00:11:44.375
All the best.

132
00:11:44.458 --> 00:11:45.291
Yes.

133
00:11:45.375 --> 00:11:46.208
Blessing.

134
00:11:46.291 --> 00:11:47.125
Yes.

135
00:11:47.208 --> 00:11:50.166
You get to live and enjoy the place.

136
00:11:50.250 --> 00:11:51.416
- Amen.
- Lucky you.

137
00:11:51.500 --> 00:11:53.958
Ajayi. my friend.

138
00:11:54.041 --> 00:11:54.958
I greet you.

139
00:11:55.625 --> 00:11:57.083
Friend. how are you?

140
00:11:58.708 --> 00:11:59.583
Thank God.

141
00:11:59.666 --> 00:12:01.625
You are well. aren't you?

142
00:12:04.541 --> 00:12:05.500
Oyedeji.

143
00:12:11.625 --> 00:12:12.750
Wait a minute.

144
00:12:13.250 --> 00:12:16.708
is someone else building
a house in front of my eyes?

145
00:12:18.916 --> 00:12:25.125
Impossible. I can't bear to watch that.

146
00:12:27.041 --> 00:12:28.291
- Agunbiade?
- Yes?

147
00:12:29.125 --> 00:12:29.958
Agunbiade.

148
00:12:31.625 --> 00:12:33.125
Why are you being hard on yourself?

149
00:12:35.208 --> 00:12:37.291
Will suicide solve anything?

150
00:12:41.083 --> 00:12:43.166
Living long is good.

151
00:12:43.250 --> 00:12:48.083
Not like this! Not like this. the object of ridicule.
Let me go.

152
00:12:48.166 --> 00:12:49.916
Where are you going? Give me this.

153
00:12:50.000 --> 00:12:51.416
- Ajayi. please.
- Anna.

154
00:12:51.500 --> 00:12:53.375
The poison.

155
00:12:54.125 --> 00:12:56.166
that your father was going to drink.

156
00:12:56.750 --> 00:12:58.916
He didn't listen to me.

157
00:12:59.625 --> 00:13:00.666
Dad. is that true?

158
00:13:01.791 --> 00:13:03.958
Do you want to kill yourself for a house?

159
00:13:05.208 --> 00:13:07.458
God will give you another house.

160
00:13:08.666 --> 00:13:11.750
Father. let's leave this in God's hands.

161
00:13:11.833 --> 00:13:12.916
What do you mean?

162
00:13:13.500 --> 00:13:14.833
Can't you hear Moren?

163
00:13:14.916 --> 00:13:17.375
I'll make sure they still get paid.

164
00:13:17.458 --> 00:13:18.750
I met them.

165
00:13:18.833 --> 00:13:20.750
and I said they'll pay.

166
00:13:20.833 --> 00:13:23.416
In Lagos I go straight away
to see my lawyer.

167
00:13:24.583 --> 00:13:29.083
You should tell us
before you do anything like that.

168
00:13:29.166 --> 00:13:30.208
Oyewale.

169
00:13:30.708 --> 00:13:35.458
they don't work.
but they take from others just like that.

170
00:13:35.541 --> 00:13:37.125
So we destroy them.

171
00:13:38.291 --> 00:13:41.041
Have you heard of untouchables?

172
00:13:41.750 --> 00:13:42.708
They are like that.

173
00:13:43.375 --> 00:13:45.166
They are like their fathers.

174
00:13:45.250 --> 00:13:47.041
When it comes to money.

175
00:13:47.833 --> 00:13:50.250
they don't even recognise their own son.

176
00:13:52.833 --> 00:13:55.958
Chief Otun made a point the other day.

177
00:13:56.541 --> 00:13:58.541
This land belongs to God -

178
00:13:58.625 --> 00:14:00.000
and those who know its history.

179
00:14:00.083 --> 00:14:02.250
Your ancestors should have told you.
that the land...

180
00:14:02.333 --> 00:14:04.125
does not belong to the Ogunladen family.

181
00:14:05.000 --> 00:14:06.583
- Chief.
- Yes?

182
00:14:07.208 --> 00:14:09.000
You just want to steal again.

183
00:14:09.833 --> 00:14:12.416
You have taken land from us
piece by piece...

184
00:14:12.500 --> 00:14:14.541
on questionable grounds.

185
00:14:14.625 --> 00:14:17.000
You will not take this land in my lifetime.

186
00:14:17.083 --> 00:14:20.166
You will not take this in my lifetime.
I'll send Ogun after you!

187
00:14:20.250 --> 00:14:23.666
Ogun!
First of the gods. Lord of the earth!

188
00:14:23.750 --> 00:14:25.875
- The owner of the water...
- Ogunlana.

189
00:14:25.958 --> 00:14:27.666
- Dad.
- Let's resolve this in moderation.

190
00:14:27.750 --> 00:14:29.375
Dad. we can't.

191
00:14:29.458 --> 00:14:32.291
Usutan Ogunin
against the greedy chiefs.

192
00:14:32.375 --> 00:14:35.166
Oh. Ogun!

193
00:14:35.250 --> 00:14:36.541
Wipe them off the face of the earth!

194
00:14:36.625 --> 00:14:38.333
Ogun...

195
00:14:39.083 --> 00:14:41.791
- You killed him!
- My son.

196
00:14:41.875 --> 00:14:43.958
God.

197
00:14:44.041 --> 00:14:46.500
- you fought for us.
- Why are we chiefs?

198
00:14:46.583 --> 00:14:49.291
We drink wine and have dinner
with the leaders.

199
00:14:49.375 --> 00:14:52.291
He does what we want.
before we even ask.

200
00:14:53.000 --> 00:14:54.750
Shall we ask the Ogun to destroy them?

201
00:14:54.833 --> 00:14:56.458
Let them be.

202
00:14:56.541 --> 00:14:57.958
They will learn from this.

203
00:14:58.041 --> 00:14:59.791
But still...

204
00:14:59.875 --> 00:15:03.166
No. Let's take care of your father.

205
00:15:03.666 --> 00:15:07.125
Or if you're ready.
maybe you can take her with you.

206
00:15:09.666 --> 00:15:10.916
Dad.

207
00:15:11.833 --> 00:15:13.291
would you come to Lagos with us?

208
00:15:15.500 --> 00:15:16.333
En.

209
00:15:17.500 --> 00:15:19.416
En.

210
00:15:26.041 --> 00:15:27.000
Stop crying.

211
00:15:28.250 --> 00:15:29.166
Stop crying.

212
00:15:29.250 --> 00:15:31.500
- They will not survive this.
- I heard you.

213
00:15:31.583 --> 00:15:32.833
Okay.

214
00:15:32.916 --> 00:15:34.791
- Calm your mind.
- Okay.

215
00:15:37.916 --> 00:15:39.916
God still has something for you.

216
00:15:40.000 --> 00:15:40.958
Okay.

217
00:15:41.041 --> 00:15:42.083
Calm your mind.

218
00:15:42.958 --> 00:15:43.875
Stop crying.

219
00:15:45.208 --> 00:15:46.125
Okay.

220
00:15:48.125 --> 00:15:51.416
Yes. I'm already sick of everything.

221
00:15:53.291 --> 00:15:55.041
In a village with laws.

222
00:15:55.916 --> 00:15:58.041
Are we just going to watch from the sidelines?

223
00:15:58.541 --> 00:15:59.916
That's what hurts me the most.

224
00:16:00.708 --> 00:16:03.666
The ones I confided in.
told me only to trust God.

225
00:16:04.750 --> 00:16:09.791
I heard that the chiefs have the power
and they enjoy the suffering of others.

226
00:16:09.875 --> 00:16:11.416
- Really?
- Yes.

227
00:16:14.250 --> 00:16:15.875
Just destroy someone else's house.

228
00:16:15.958 --> 00:16:19.708
- to sell the land.
- Very devious.

229
00:16:22.375 --> 00:16:24.208
I am so sad.

230
00:16:24.291 --> 00:16:25.291
I know.

231
00:16:26.125 --> 00:16:28.041
We were not informed of anything.

232
00:16:28.125 --> 00:16:29.833
We must not just keep silent.

233
00:16:29.916 --> 00:16:31.916
Yes.

234
00:16:32.875 --> 00:16:35.916
You have no money
But you say the idea is

235
00:16:36.000 --> 00:16:41.625
Well to hell with that idea

236
00:16:41.708 --> 00:16:44.666
You lovers of pleasure

237
00:16:44.750 --> 00:16:46.250
Enjoy yourselves

238
00:16:47.166 --> 00:16:50.250
We are the best of the best. so

239
00:16:50.333 --> 00:16:52.375
- Listen.
- I said it already

240
00:16:52.458 --> 00:16:55.958
- Listen. you can eat...
- We are the best of the best

241
00:16:56.041 --> 00:16:58.958
- ...whatever you want.
- We are the best of the best

242
00:16:59.041 --> 00:17:00.208
- You know what?
- Well?

243
00:17:00.791 --> 00:17:04.083
I will spoil you with pleasures.

244
00:17:05.625 --> 00:17:07.083
This is just the beginning.

245
00:17:07.750 --> 00:17:08.833
- Yes.
- Listen.

246
00:17:09.500 --> 00:17:10.625
I understand what you are saying.

247
00:17:10.708 --> 00:17:11.916
Yes.

248
00:17:12.000 --> 00:17:13.041
You can predict tomorrow -

249
00:17:13.125 --> 00:17:14.333
- today.
- Yes.

250
00:17:14.416 --> 00:17:18.041
We understand.
what wonders you will do as King.

251
00:17:19.583 --> 00:17:20.833
No one will stop you.

252
00:17:20.916 --> 00:17:23.166
This is just the beginning!

253
00:17:23.666 --> 00:17:25.250
I will spoil you with pleasures.

254
00:17:25.875 --> 00:17:27.750
My Lord. I understand.

255
00:17:28.333 --> 00:17:31.291
- My Lord.
- Enjoy.

256
00:17:31.375 --> 00:17:36.625
You know you'll be spending the night here.

257
00:17:36.708 --> 00:17:38.291
No one is going home today.

258
00:17:38.791 --> 00:17:39.625
- Really?
- Yes.

259
00:17:39.708 --> 00:17:41.000
We were not prepared.

260
00:17:41.083 --> 00:17:46.500
I have prepared the beds and everything for you.

261
00:17:47.125 --> 00:17:49.416
The King asked me to sing

262
00:17:49.500 --> 00:17:54.083
We greet you
Greetings. Otun and Olukosi

263
00:17:54.166 --> 00:17:56.166
We greet you

264
00:17:56.250 --> 00:17:58.916
Greetings. Akin and Iyalode

265
00:17:59.000 --> 00:18:01.791
Here are the blankets.
to keep you warm.

266
00:18:01.875 --> 00:18:05.833
I have the power to do what I want...

267
00:18:05.916 --> 00:18:11.833
We will stay warm. but what about Iyalode?

268
00:18:11.916 --> 00:18:13.416
Wasn't he cold?

269
00:18:14.875 --> 00:18:18.083
I am good to be.
